Russian President Vladimir Putin on Monday awarded Chinese Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to Russia Li Hui with the Order of Friendship. The corresponding presidential decree was published on Russia's official legal information portal. According to the document, the ambassador was awarded for his contribution to strengthening friendship and cooperation between the two countries as well as his fruitful work on the convergence and mutual enrichment of their cultures. A number of other Russian and foreign citizens were awarded with the Order of Friendship and the Pushkin Medal by the same decree. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Actress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame starDelegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growth